<doc id="85326" wikidata="Q3086735" url="?curid=85326" title="Fraus">
<text>In Roman mythology, Fraus was the goddess of personification of treachery and fraud.

She was daughter of Orcus and Night (Nyx). She was depicted with a woman&#x27;s face, the body of a snake, and on her tail the sting of a scorpion.

Fraus is an alternative name for Mercury, the god of theft (among other things). She is alternatively described as Mercury&#x27;s helper.. Her Greek equivalent was Apate.

